ZERO ENGINE DEVELOPMENT ROADMAP
===============================

PHASE 1: CORE RENDERING & UI
-----------------------------
[x] Vulkan renderer initialization
[x] Instanced rendering pipeline
[x] Model loading (glTF/GLB)
[x] Texture loading
[x] ECS foundation
[x] Camera system
[x] Basic ImGui integration

PHASE 2: ANIMATION SYSTEM
-------------------------
[ ] Skeletal animation
    [ ] Bone hierarchy loading
    [ ] Skinning shader (GPU skinning)
    [ ] Animation clip loading
    [ ] Animation playback (play/pause/stop)
    [ ] Animation blending
    [ ] Animation state machine
    [ ] Root motion support

[ ] Procedural animation
    [ ] IK (inverse kinematics)
    [ ] Look-at constraints
    [ ] Procedural walk cycles

[ ] Animation tools
    [ ] Timeline scrubbing in editor
    [ ] Animation preview
    [ ] Blend tree visualization

PHASE 3: VISUAL POLISH
----------------------
[ ] Lighting
    [ ] Point lights
    [ ] Spot lights
    [ ] Directional lights with shadows
    [ ] Shadow mapping (cascaded for large scenes)
    [ ] Soft shadows (PCF/PCSS)

[ ] Materials
    [ ] PBR pipeline (metallic/roughness)
    [ ] Normal mapping
    [ ] Emission maps
    [ ] Ambient occlusion
    [ ] Material editor in ImGui

[ ] Post-processing
    [ ] HDR rendering
    [ ] Tonemapping (ACES, Reinhard)
    [ ] Bloom
    [ ] SSAO (screen-space ambient occlusion)
    [ ] Anti-aliasing (FXAA/TAA)
    [ ] Motion blur
    [ ] Depth of field
    [ ] Color grading/LUT

[ ] Environment
    [ ] Skybox/cubemaps
    [ ] Reflection probes
    [ ] Fog (linear/exponential)
    [ ] Particle system (GPU compute)

[ ] Optimization
    [ ] Frustum culling
    [ ] Occlusion culling
    [ ] LOD system
    [ ] Texture streaming
    [ ] Compute shader batching

PHASE 4: PHYSICS
----------------
[ ] Physics engine integration (Jolt, Bullet, or PhysX)
    [ ] Rigid body dynamics
    [ ] Collision detection
    [ ] Collision shapes (box, sphere, capsule, mesh, convex hull)
    [ ] Triggers/sensors
    [ ] Physics materials (friction, restitution)

[ ] Constraints
    [ ] Fixed joints
    [ ] Hinge joints
    [ ] Slider joints
    [ ] Spring joints
    [ ] Ragdolls

[ ] Character physics
    [ ] Character controller
    [ ] Ground detection
    [ ] Slopes and stairs
    [ ] Moving platforms

[ ] Advanced
    [ ] Raycasting/shape casting
    [ ] Continuous collision detection
    [ ] Physics layers/masks
    [ ] Debug visualization (wireframes)

PHASE 5: SCRIPTING
------------------
[ ] Scripting language integration (Lua, Wren, or C# via Mono)
    [ ] Script component
    [ ] Hot reloading
    [ ] API bindings (entity, transform, input, physics)

[ ] Script lifecycle
    [ ] init() / start()
    [ ] update(dt)
    [ ] fixedUpdate(dt) for physics
    [ ] onCollision / onTrigger
    [ ] onDestroy()

[ ] Editor integration
    [ ] Script creation templates
    [ ] Syntax error display
    [ ] Breakpoint debugging (optional)
    [ ] Exposed variables in inspector

[ ] Native scripting alternative
    [ ] C++ component hot-reload via DLL/SO
    [ ] Reflection system for properties

PHASE 6: GAME FEATURES
----------------------
[ ] Audio
    [ ] Audio engine (OpenAL, miniaudio, or FMOD)
    [ ] 3D positional audio
    [ ] Music playback
    [ ] Sound effects
    [ ] Audio mixer/channels
    [ ] Reverb zones

[ ] Input
    [ ] Input action mapping
    [ ] Gamepad support
    [ ] Rebindable controls
    [ ] Input recording/playback

[ ] AI
    [ ] Navigation mesh generation
    [ ] Pathfinding (A*)
    [ ] Behavior trees
    [ ] State machines
    [ ] Steering behaviors

[ ] UI system (in-game)
    [ ] Canvas/screen-space UI
    [ ] Buttons, sliders, text
    [ ] UI anchoring/layouts
    [ ] UI animations
    [ ] Localization support

[ ] Scene management
    [ ] Scene serialization (save/load)
    [ ] Scene transitions
    [ ] Prefab system
    [ ] Additive scene loading

[ ] Networking (optional)
    [ ] Client-server architecture
    [ ] State synchronization
    [ ] Lag compensation

